    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="108"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Hopkins Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Presidents Special Assistant</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chinese Foreign Minister</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Soong</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-19">May 19,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Dr. Soong</hi>: Apropos of your note of May 18th,<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d108fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_290">p. 290</ref>.</note> the
                    only amendment I have to suggest relates to paragraph 5 of your proposed wire to
                    the Generalissimo. I think the following wording would more appropriately
                    indicate the President’s purposes <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“5. The President told me that it is the position of the United States
                            that <gloss target="#t_Anakim1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Anakim</hi>
                            </gloss> will be undertaken this winter in conjunction with the British.
                            Definite plans for this project are now being considered from the
                            viewpoint of the allotment of tonnage and special equipment, preliminary
                            to detailed plans for each phase of the operation, which will be
                            communicated to me for your consideration as they are prepared.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Very cordially yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry L. Hopkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
